episodes.title: Epstein files reveal Trump jet travel details | 7NEWS
episodes.description:
The US Department of Justice has released nearly 30,000 pages of documents related to Jeffrey Epstein, revealing Donald Trump travelled on Epstein's private jet at least eight times in the 1990s, including four flights with convicted sex trafficker Ghislaine Maxwell. A letter signed by J. Epstein sent to convicted sex offender Larry Nassar contains crude references to Trump, though the FBI has labelled it fake, and the White House emphasises the President has not been accused of any wrongdoing. The documents also include email exchanges suggesting connections between Epstein's associate Maxwell and former Prince Andrew, though he has not been charged with any crimes.

episodes.title: Congress threatens contempt charges over Epstein files | 7NEWS
episodes.description:
The US Department of Justice faces bipartisan congressional pressure over its incomplete release of Jeffrey Epstein files by the December 19 deadline. Deputy Attorney General Todd Blanche defends the delay as necessary to protect victims, while Republican Thomas Massie and Democrat Ro Khanna threaten to hold Attorney General Pam Bondi in inherent contempt. The controversy includes nearly 700 completely redacted pages and temporarily removed photos, including one showing Epstein with President Donald Trump.
